race.comment: WOOTTEN HYDE (7) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up at his past couple before the spell and strikes a very winnable contest here. Guthmann-Chester has been in the irons for both placings and sticks here. Rates the testing material. TORQUE TO BE SURE (4) was well in the betting when resuming but just missed the frame on that occasion. Where there's smoke there's fire and must be included in calculations. LADY MILAN (12) draws the inside marble and should give backers a sight. ANDI DON'T CARE (8) is first-up here but has revved up for this with two recent trials and must be respected out of the Gollan yard. In the mix at odds. URBAN LAD (5) next best.
